The paper deals with incentivized exploration in multi-armed bandits, which is a problem in machine learning and game theory. The paper discusses the design of incentive-compatible algorithms, which is a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the sample complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper uses Bayesian methods, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
